===== abs =====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cstdlib>
int abs( int num );
</source>
}}

The abs() function returns the absolute value of ''num''. For example:

<source lang=cpp>
int magic_number = 10;
cout << "Enter a guess: ";
cin >> x;
cout << "Your guess was " << abs( magic_number - x ) << " away from the magic number." << endl; 
</source>

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fabs|fabs]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/labs|labs]]

