==== freopen ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cstdio>
FILE *freopen( const char *fname, const char *mode, FILE *stream );
</source>
}}

The freopen() function is used to reassign an existing stream to a different file and mode. After a call to this function, the given file stream will refer to fname  with access given by mode. The return value of freopen() is the new stream, or '''NULL''' if there is an error.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fclose|fclose]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fopen|fopen]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== fread ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cstdio>
int fread( void *buffer, size_t size, size_t num, FILE *stream );
</source>
}}

The function fread() reads num number of objects (where each object is size bytes) and places them into the array pointed to by buffer. The data comes from the given input stream. The return value of the function is the number of things read. You can use [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/feof|feof]]() or [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ferror|ferror]]() to figure out if an error occurs.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fflush|fflush]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fgetc|fgetc]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fopen|fopen]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fputc|fputc]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fscanf|fscanf]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fwrite|fwrite]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/getc|getc]]

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

==== fputc ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cstdio>
int fputc( int ch, FILE *stream );
</source>
}}

The function fputc() writes the given character ch to the given output stream. The return value is the character, unless there is an error, in which case the return value is '''EOF'''.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fgetc|fgetc]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fopen|fopen]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fprintf|fprintf]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fread|fread]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/fwrite|fwrite]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/getc|getc]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/getchar|getchar]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/putc|putc]]

