==Limits to Infinity==
Evaluate the following limits or state that the limit does not exist.
{{question-answer|question=27. <math> \lim_{x\to \infty} \frac{-x + \pi}{x^2 + 3x + 2} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>0</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=28. <math> \lim_{x\to -\infty} \frac{x^2+2x+1}{3x^2+1} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{1}{3}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=29. <math> \lim_{x\to -\infty} \frac{3x^2 + x}{2x^2 - 15} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{3}{2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=30. <math> \lim_{x\to -\infty} 3x^2-2x+1 </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\infty</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=31. <math> \lim_{x\to \infty} \frac{2x^2-32}{x^3-64} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>0</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=32. <math> \lim_{x\to \infty} 6 </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>6</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=33. <math> \lim_{x\to \infty} \frac{3x^2 +4x}{x^4+2} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>0</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=34. <math> \lim_{x\to -\infty} \frac{2x+3x^2+1}{2x^2+3} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>\frac{3}{2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=35. <math> \lim_{x\to -\infty} \frac{x^3-3x^2+1}{3x^2+x+5} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>-\infty</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=36. <math> \lim_{x\to \infty} \frac{x^2+2}{x^3-2} </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>0</math>}}}}
{{noprint|[[Calculus/Limits/Solutions#Limits to Infinity|Solutions]]}}

==Limits of Piecewise Functions==
Evaluate the following limits or state that the limit does not exist.<br/>
</br>
37. Consider the function
: <math> f(x) = \begin{cases} (x-2)^2 & \mbox{if }x<2 \\ x-3 & \mbox{if }x\geq 2. \end{cases} </math>
{{question-answer|question=a. <math> \lim_{x\to 2^-}f(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>0</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. <math> \lim_{x\to 2^+}f(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>-1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. <math> \lim_{x\to 2}f(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|The limit does not exist}}}}
<br/>
38. Consider the function
: <math> g(x) = \begin{cases} -2x+1 & \mbox{if }x\leq 0 \\ x+1 & \mbox{if }0<x<4 \\ x^2 +2 & \mbox{if }x \geq 4. \end{cases} </math>
{{question-answer|question=a. <math> \lim_{x\to 4^+} g(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>18</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. <math> \lim_{x\to 4^-} g(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>5</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. <math> \lim_{x\to 0^+} g(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=d. <math> \lim_{x\to 0^-} g(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=e. <math> \lim_{x\to 0} g(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=f. <math> \lim_{x\to 1} g(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>2</math>}}}}
<br/>
39. Consider the function
: <math> h(x) = \begin{cases} 2x-3 & \mbox{if }x<2 \\ 8 & \mbox{if }x=2 \\ -x+3 & \mbox{if } x>2. \end{cases} </math>
{{question-answer|question=a. <math> \lim_{x\to 0} h(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>-3</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=b. <math> \lim_{x\to 2^-} h(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=c. <math> \lim_{x\to 2^+} h(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>1</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=d. <math> \lim_{x\to 2} h(x) </math>|answer={{noprint|<math>1</math>}}}}
{{noprint|[[Calculus/Limits/Solutions#Limits of Piecewise Functions|Solutions]]}}

