[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] finds this spell in the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Potions|Potions]] text that belonged to the Half-Blood Prince. He uses it at one point in the story to silence [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Peeves|Peeves]], who is loudly commentating a fight between [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Dobby|Dobby]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Kreacher|Kreacher]]. We also guess that this is the spell left in the entrance to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Grimmauld Place|Number 12, Grimmauld Place]] by [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Alastor Moody|Mad-Eye Moody]] as part of the attempt to prevent [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Severus Snape|Snape]]'s entrance.
