{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Oppugno| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Jinx)| features=Causes creatures to attack| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Half-Blood Prince|''Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Oppugno''''' apparently causes creatures to hate the target of the spell. The result is that the creatures influenced by the spell will attack its subject.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
We only see this spell used once. [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]], having seen [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ron Weasley|Ron]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Lavender Brown|Lavender]] locked in one of their embraces, has retreated to a disused classroom, where she has moodily [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Avis|created a flock of canaries]] which are circling her. Ron and Lavender, apparently seeking some privacy, also enter the classroom; Lavender quickly backs out, but Ron stays to exchange some words with Hermione. Hermione, angered, uses the spell to set the canaries on Ron as she is leaving.
There is mention later that Ron still bears the scars of the canary beaks and talons.
== Analysis ==
It is uncertain whether this spell would work on any creature, or only on creatures that the caster has created. As we see this spell only the one time, we can only guess at its effects and applicability.
