{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Protean Charm| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Charm)| features=Makes objects similar across distance| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Order of the Phoenix|''Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix'']]}}
== Overview ==
The '''''Protean Charm''''' makes multiple objects act as if they are the same object – changes made to one object appear on all of them.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
In order to make it easier to contact all the members of [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/Dumbledore's Army|Dumbledore's Army]], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]] creates a large number of false [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Money|Galleons]]. These Galleons are charmed such that, once the date of the next meeting is determined, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] can change one Galleon to show that date, and all the others will similarly change, and heat up to let their holders know that they have changed. [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Terry Boot|Terry Boot]] recognizes the charm as a Protean Charm, and is impressed: this is [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/NEWT exams|NEWT-level magic]].
A parallel is drawn to the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Dark Mark|Dark Mark]] tattoo that Death Eaters wear on their left forearm, and Hermione indicates that she had not thought that Harry would want to inflict pain on his prospective students.
